      "span_text": "In previous studies, both young and old mice learned the simple discrimination (choosing the correct arm) and avoidance (running to the correct goal within 5 s) components of the task on the first session, but required up to 30 or more sessions before they were able to efficiently use information presented only on the first trial of each session (a working memory requirement) to avoid all subsequent shocks"
